@startuml LLM - Strategy Pattern and Rendering

' ==============================================================================
' LLM Module
' Shows Strategy Pattern for LLM clients and response rendering
' ==============================================================================

!define STRATEGY_COLOR #90EE90

skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor White
    BorderColor Black
}

' ==============================================================================
' Strategy Pattern - LLM Client
' ==============================================================================

interface LLMClientTrait <<Strategy>> STRATEGY_COLOR {
    <b>Basic Query</b>
    + {async} query(&self, text: &str): Result<String>
    __
    <b>Extended Queries</b>
    + {async} query_with_context(&self, text: &str, \\n    context: Option<String>): Result<String>
    + {async} query_with_history(&self, text: &str, \\n    command_history: &[String]): Result<String>
}

class HttpLLMClient <<Strategy>> STRATEGY_COLOR {
    - base_url: String
    - client: reqwest::Client
    __
    <b>Construction</b>
    + new(base_url: String): Self
    + with_timeout(base_url: String, timeout_secs: u64): Result<Self>
}

class MockLLMClient <<Strategy>> STRATEGY_COLOR {
    __
    <b>Construction</b>
    + new(): Self
    __
    <b>Behavior</b>
    Returns mock responses for testing:
    - Docker queries → Docker info
    - Kubernetes → kubectl examples
    - Generic → DevOps tips
}

LLMClientTrait <|.. HttpLLMClient : implements
LLMClientTrait <|.. MockLLMClient : implements

' ==============================================================================
' HTTP Client DTOs
' ==============================================================================

class LLMRequest {
    + query: String
    + context: Option<String>
}

class LLMResponse {
    + text: String
    + metadata: Option<serde_json::Value>
}

HttpLLMClient ..> LLMRequest : <<sends>>
HttpLLMClient ..> LLMResponse : <<receives>>

' ==============================================================================
' Response Rendering
' ==============================================================================

class ResponseRenderer {
    - syntax_set: SyntaxSet
    - theme_set: ThemeSet
    __
    <b>Construction</b>
    + new(): Self
    __
    <b>Rendering</b>
    + render(&self, text: &str): Vec<String>
    __
    <b>Internal Processing</b>
    - format_inline(&self, line: &str): String
    - highlight_code(&self, lines: &[String], lang: &str): Vec<String>
}

ResponseRenderer ..> LLMClientTrait : <<uses>>

note top of LLMClientTrait
  <b>Strategy Pattern</b>

  Permette switching tra:

  1. <b>MockLLMClient</b>
     - Per development/testing
     - No network richiesto
     - Risposte pre-programmate

  2. <b>HttpLLMClient</b>
     - Per produzione
     - REST API a LLM backend
     - Configurabile via INFRAWARE_LLM_URL

  Future: OpenAI, Anthropic, local models
end note

note bottom of HttpLLMClient
  <b>HTTP Client Implementation</b>

  Usa reqwest per chiamate async:
  - POST {base_url}/query
  - JSON request/response
  - Timeout configurabile
  - Error handling per network issues

  Environment variable:
  export INFRAWARE_LLM_URL="http://localhost:8000"
end note

note top of MockLLMClient
  <b>Mock Implementation</b>

  Pattern matching su keywords:

  "docker" → Info su Docker containers
  "kubernetes" → kubectl cheatsheet
  "aws" → AWS CLI examples
  default → Generic DevOps tips

  Usato automaticamente se
  INFRAWARE_LLM_URL non impostato
end note

note right of ResponseRenderer
  <b>Markdown & Syntax Highlighting</b>

  <b>Supported Features (M1):</b>
  ✓ Code blocks with syntax highlighting
  ✓ Inline code: `code`
  ✓ Bold: **text**
  ✓ Basic formatting

  <b>Languages supported:</b>
  - Rust
  - Python
  - Bash/Shell
  - JSON
  - YAML
  - JavaScript/TypeScript
  - Many more via syntect

  <b>Deferred to M2/M3:</b>
  - Tables
  - Images
  - Complex markdown
  - Links
end note

note bottom of ResponseRenderer
  <b>Rendering Pipeline</b>

  1. Split text into lines
  2. Detect code block markers (```)
  3. Accumulate code lines
  4. Apply syntax highlighting (syntect)
  5. Format inline markdown
  6. Return Vec<String> for display

  Uses syntect with default theme
  and syntax sets for highlighting
end note

' ==============================================================================
' Usage Example
' ==============================================================================

package "Usage in NaturalLanguageOrchestrator" {
    class NaturalLanguageOrchestrator {
        - llm_client: Arc<dyn LLMClientTrait>
        - renderer: ResponseRenderer
        __
        + {async} handle_query(...)
    }
}

NaturalLanguageOrchestrator o-- LLMClientTrait
NaturalLanguageOrchestrator *-- ResponseRenderer

@enduml
